So far this year, more than 670 people in 22 states have gotten measles.
Doctors say the primary way to prevent the virus is to get the vaccine.
This latest outbreak started last year and is concentrated in a few states – New York, New Jersey, Washington, and California.
When she recently stopped by Skimm HQ, we asked her to weigh in on the outbreak.
